'''Bongwater''' (noun)

The water through which smoke is filtered in a bong or water pipe.  Generally described as disgusting, rancid, nasty and evil.  Varies in color from clear (freshly changed) to a murky grey-black color.  

While the water cools down the smoke before the user's inhalation, it serves the dual purpose of also catching the ash, therefore it should be changed frequently.  

'''Example:'''  ''Dude, you should really change that '''bongwater.'''  I can smell it from six feet away!''